HEADWORD: dethrone
<hw>de*throne"</hw> <pr>(d⟦esl⟧*thr⟦omac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Dethroned</conjf>
<pr>(d⟦esl⟧*thr⟦omac⟧nd")</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Dethroning</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>de-</ets> +
<ets>throne</ets>: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧tr⟦ocir⟧ner</ets>; pref.
<ets>d⟦eacute⟧-</ets> (L. <ets>dis-</ets>) + <ets>tr⟦ocir⟧ne</ets>
throne. See <er>Throne</er>.]</ety> <def>To remove or drive from a
throne; to depose; to divest of supreme authority and dignity.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The Protector was <xex>dethroned</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
